    {
      "type": "header",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Murine (Endemic) Typhus"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Murine typhus is caused by Rickettsia typhi and is transmitted by fleas, primarily the rat flea (Xenopsylla cheopis). It is a milder illness than epidemic typhus."
    },
    {
      "type": "header",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Clinical Manifestations"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Clinical presentation is similar to epidemic typhus but less severe. Symptoms include fever, headache, and rash. The rash is typically maculopapular and less extensive than in epidemic typhus."
    },
    {
      "type": "header",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Diagnosis"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Diagnosis is made by serology (IFA)."
    },
    {
      "type": "header",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Treatment"
    },
    {
